# CBT Application Upgrade Implementation Plan

This plan details the architecture, design, and step-by-step changes required to upgrade the Computer-Based Testing (CBT) application for **Faith Immaculate Academy**. It leverages Google Gemini AI, psychometrics, and advanced report capabilities to transform a standard testing application into a premium academic platform.

---

## Proposed System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Client-Side [Frontend (React + Recharts + Lucide)]
        Dashboard[Admin & Student Portals]
        SettingsUI[Settings Page - Results Toggles]
        AnalyticsUI[Analytics Dashboard - Psychometrics & Trajectory]
        ImporterUI[Smart Importer - Drag & Drop / Preview Grid]
        PrintUI[PDF Printable Reports - Student Dossier & Broadscore]
    end

    subgraph Server-Side [Backend (Express.js + Gemini API + Mammoth)]
        UploadAPI[File Upload API]
        GeminiAPI[Gemini SDK parsing engine]
        StorageAPI[MemStorage adapter & student lists]
    end

    ImporterUI -->|Upload .docx/.txt| UploadAPI
    UploadAPI -->|Extract Text| GeminiAPI
    GeminiAPI -->|Return Structured JSON| ImporterUI
    ImporterUI -->|Review/Correct & Bulk Submit| StorageAPI
    SettingsUI -->|Toggle score formats & headers| Dashboard
    StorageAPI -->|Metrics data| AnalyticsUI
```

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key Architectural Decisions & Requirements:**
> 1. **Gemini SDK Key**: The Smart Question Importer backend endpoint (`POST /api/questions/import-ai`) relies on `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY` being set in the environment. We will support standard API key extraction from the process environment.
> 2. **Print System Integration**: The student profile summary print report is converted from a standard browser screenshot into a beautiful, styled PDF document rendered in a sandboxed print window, maintaining absolute design fidelity.
> 3. **Consolidated Reports vs. Broadsheets**:
>    - **Consolidated Report**: Batch printout summarizing all completed exams for one or more selected students.
>    - **Broadsheet/Score Sheet**: Class-wide or department-wide summary table displaying scores per subject/exam for multiple students, filtered properly.

